</P>
<P>
   MITCH-MARINES (Chinandega, Nicaragua _ Six hundred bulldozers,
graders, jeeps and trucks, painted camouflage green and driven by
U.S. Marines with crew cuts, rolled out this week from the Pacific
Coast port of Corinto in 30 small caravans, bound for the hard-hit
northern provinces of Esteli, Matagalpa, Jinotega and Nueva
Segovia, where Hurricane Mitch's rains washed out roads and bridges
and demolished homes, crops and livestock. By TYCHE HENDRICKS.
