Sunday afternoon, on an NFL sideline. He threw three interceptions
and was benched. Then everything boiled over for the young
Pittsburgh Steeler, and he lost control. Quarterbacks keep melting
down. A year ago, it was Washington's exasperated Gus Frerotte
banging his head against a wall and giving himself a concussion.
Once the toast of D.C., now he's just toast. By GWEN KNAPP.
</P>
<P>
   GLF-COLF-COMPUTER (Clifton Park, N.Y.) _ John Pritchard wanted
to play exotic golf games with complicated scoring methods such as
Nassau, Scramble, Vegas and others that are fun for those who like
to bet a few dollars on the side. But he couldn't keep up with the
scoring. So he invented a computer program that fits on certain
types of hand-held computers that allows individuals and golf
foursomes to keep score of one or even multiple golf games. By ALAN
D. ABBEY.
</P>
