<SLUG> BC-SHARPS-MUSIC-LADN </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
TO EVERYTHING THERE IS A SEASON
</HEADLINE>
 (For use by NYTimes News Service clients) 
By FRED SHUSTER 
c.1998 Los Angeles Daily News  
<TEXT>
<P>
   LOS ANGELES _ Landing a song on the soundtrack of a box-office
smash can change Everything.
</P>
<P>
   But the six members of the hard-working Virginia group known as
Everything are keeping feet planted firmly on terra firma despite
the fact that their track, ``Hooch,'' was picked for use in Adam
Sandler's hit comedy, ``The Waterboy.''
</P>
<P>
   Together for eight years, Everything has been dubbed the
hardest-working band in the biz. The band has been on the road
steadily for the last five years, playing more than 200 shows
annually, including dates with acts as diverse as A Tribe Called
Quest, Cracker, Dave Matthews Band and even the Who. In addition,
the imaginative pop-alternative outfit is one of the only bands to
have opened for Phish.
</P>
<P>
   The concert-industry mag Pollstar ranked Everything, under its
own steam, among the 50 highest-grossing tours for four months
straight two years ago. Today, the group is on the road supporting
its major-label debut, ``Super Natural'' (Blackbird/Sire), which
has spent more than five months in Billboard's Heatseekers chart
for new or developing acts.
</P>
<P>
   ``There's so much music coming out every year, but somehow the
good stuff always shines through,'' said Everything
singer-guitarist Craig Honeycutt. ``Once you get to a certain level
with your music, you realize there's very good stuff in every
genre. The walls start to fall away, and your ears open up. We can
say we're influenced by a lot of different types of music now.''
</P>
<P>
   MY FAVORITE MARTIN: We asked recently retired Beatles producer
George Martin what he thought of today's rock scene on the 30th
anniversary of the release of ``The Beatles,'' universally known as
``The White Album.''
</P>
<P>
   The album has just been issued in a limited-edition CD package
that re-creates all the elements of the original 1968 double album
in scaled-down fashion.
</P>
<P>
   ``It's a tough music world out there now,'' Martin said. ``I'm
so glad I'm not in it. The competition is so great _ there's an
awful lot of good musicians around, and they're all clamoring for
attention. It's fairly significant that the record companies are
reissuing so much old stuff. They're marketing nostalgia.''
</P>
<P>
   Martin said at least one thing hasn't changed in three decades _
the importance of quality tunes.
</P>
<P>
   ``The song is the thing,'' he said. ``The Beatles wouldn't be
what they are today without that marvelous songbook.'' &QL; 
ENDIT &QL;
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
<TRAILER>
NYT-12-17-98 1427EST &QL; 
</TRAILER>
