u e &Cx13;  &Cx11;  BC-ENTERTAINMENT-NYT-BUD     12-17 0616
</HEADER>
<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-ENTERTAINMENT-NYT-BUDGET </SLUG>
  
<TEXT>
<P>
   Weekend Section stories from The New York Times News Service for
Friday, Dec. 18.
</P>
<P>
   &UR; FEATURES &LR;
</P>
<P>
   ROYAL-OPERA (London) _ The British government will bail out the
cash-poor Royal Opera House. By Sarah Lyall.
</P>
<P>
   HANSON-SCULPTURE-EXHIBIT (New York) _ A sculpture retrospective
of the late Duane Hanson at the Whitney Museum of American Art. By
Dinitia Smith.
</P>
<P>
   CHRISTMAS-DECORATION (New York) _ The spirit of Christmas
resides in Brooklyn, at 7823 12th Avenue in Dyker Heights. There,
in a four-bedroom brick row house, Peter and Janet Marcolini have
hung, strung and sprung a dazzling array of decorations for a
quarter century, each year noticeably more than the year before.
They may be running out of space, but they will never run out of
heart. By Douglas Martin.
</P>
<P>
   PARADE-THEATER-REVIEW (New York) _ ``Parade,'' a musical
directed by Harold Prince, at the Vivian Beaumont at Lincoln
Center. Reviewed by Ben Brantley.
</P>
