<DOCTYPE> NEWS STORY </DOCTYPE>
<DATE_TIME> 1998-12-17 17:27 </DATE_TIME>
<HEADER>
A5345 &Cx1f; tad-z
u w &Cx13;  &Cx11;  BC-EDWARDS-IMPEACH17-COX     12-17 0635
</HEADER>
<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-EDWARDS-IMPEACH17-COX </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
&HT;   
</HEADLINE>
   WACO'S EDWARDS TO VOTE AGAINST IMPEACHMENT
   585 words
   By EUNICE MOSCOSO
   c.1998 Cox News Service
<TEXT>
<P>
   WASHINGTON _ With an impeachment vote fast approaching and U.S.
bombs falling on Iraq, Rep. Chet Edwards, D-Texas, said Thursday he
will vote against impeaching President Clinton.
</P>
<P>
   ``I believe what the president did was indefensible and immoral,
but I do not think his actions, however wrong, reached the high
constitutional threshold for impeachment,'' the Waco representative
said.
</P>
<P>
   Edwards added he would support a ``bipartisan congressional
censure'' and that future criminal action against the president
``would be appropriate punishment for his affair and subsequent
misleading statements.''
</P>
<P>
   Republican leaders decided Thursday to begin the impeachment
debate Friday on the House floor and finish action on the four
articles of impeachment against Clinton by Saturday, even if U.S.
attacks against Iraq are ongoing.
</P>
<P>
   Edwards delivered harsh words Thursday against Republicans who
publicly questioned the timing of U.S. military strikes on Iraq.
</P>
<P>
   ``That type of unsubstantiated, personal attack against our
president at a time when brave American pilots and armed forces are
in harm's way is wrong. It is irresponsible. It does harm to the
morale of our forces in the Persian Gulf,'' he said, on the House
floor.
</P>
<P>
   Rep. Gerald Solomon, R-N.Y., and other GOP lawmakers suggested
Wednesday the president had ordered the Iraqi attack to divert
attention from the looming impeachment vote, which originally had
been scheduled for Thursday.
</P>
<P>
   Edwards said the criticism hit more people than just Clinton.
</P>
<P>
   ``I urge some of my colleagues to reconsider their ill-advised
comments from last night,'' Edwards said. ``An attack on the
integrity of this operation is in fact an attack on the integrity
of our joint chiefs.''
</P>
<P>
   In addition, Edwards quoted Defense Secretary William Cohen, a
Republican, who said Wednesday he was prepared to place 30 years of
public service on the line to say the motivation was not political.
</P>
<P>
   After Edwards concluded his statement, Speaker-elect Bob
Livingston, R-La., responded to it and others made by Democrats.
</P>
<P>
   Livingston said he ``must remind all members that although it's
permissible to debate and speak critically of the president or the
administration on matters of policy or politics, remarks and debate
may not descend to personality by arraigning the president's
personal conduct or by charging other members with having done so
off the floor.''
</P>
<P>
   Edwards said he agreed with the first part of Livingston's
statement about not allowing personal attacks against the president
but added that it was ``a real stretch'' for Livingston to say a
member didn't have the right to speak out against other members'
comments.
</P>
<P>
   ``That logic would suggest that if Joseph McCarthy could accuse
the president of being a communist, that no member of the House
would have a right to come to this body and say that that is an
irresponsible attack on the integrity of the presidency,'' he said.
</P>
<P>
   ``I cannot even imagine that the free speech rights of members
of the House could be limited in that way,'' he said.
</P>
<P>
   Despite the comments from Livingston, Edwards said he respected
the speaker-elect and that he believes Livingston will have a much
more bipartisan approach than his predecessor, Speaker Newt
Gingrich of Georgia.
</P>
<P>
   Edwards said he would continue to speak out against unfounded
accusations about the timing of U.S. military strikes against Iraq.
</P>
<P>
   ``Those kinds of statements need to stop, and they need to stop
today,'' he said. ``I stand by my statement.''
</P>
<P>
   ENDIT
</P>
<P>
   Story Filed By Cox Newspapers
</P>
