   FBN-NFLBEST _ Highlights of upcoming NFL weekend. (Pasquarelli,
Atlanta Journal-Constitution) ETA: 7 p.m.
</P>
<P>
   FBN-FALCONS-TICKETS _ ATLANTA _ Falcons season-ticket holders,
some 25,000 strong, accounted for sales of 27,000 tickets for
playoff games. Now, general public gets its chance to buy on
Saturday. (Winklejohn, Atlanta Journal-Constitution.) 9.
</P>
<P>
   FBN-FALCONS-BENNETT _ Cornelius Bennett, troubled by injured
knee, might not play vs. Lions. (Winklejohn, Atlanta
Journal-Constitution.) 9.
</P>
<P>
   FBN-FALCONS-NOTES _ Falcons notebook. (Winklejohn, Atlanta
Journal-Constitution.)
</P>
<P>
   FBC-COACHES _ Former Georgia assistant Chris Scelfo faces an
uneviable task as he prepares for his first game as Tulane's coach
_ he doesn't have much of a staff to work with. Many of the former
assistants under former coach Tommy Bowden have joined their boss
at Clemson, leaving Scelfo with a small staff to prepare for the
Liberty Bowl in two weeks. Florida will face Syracuse in the Orange
Bowl without its offensive and defensive coordinator while
Tennessee will meet Florida State in the Fiesta Bowl without its
offensive coordinator after David Cutcliffe left to become the
coach at Ole Miss. At Ole Miss, Cutcliffe won't have much of a
staff to work with as many of the former assistants followed Tommy
Tuberville to Auburn. How are teams preparing for bowls with
limited staff? (Barnhart, Atlanta Journal-Constitution)
</P>
<P>
   FBC-GASOUTHERN _ For most of his career at Georgia Southern,
Earthwind Moreland has received more notoriety for his first name
than his play on the field. But he is one of the primary reasons
that the Eagles will be playing for the Division I-AA national
championship Saturday against Massachusetts. The former walk-on is
the team's top defensive back and one of the leaders of a defense
which figures to be tested against the Minutemen. If the Eagles are
to be successful, they'll need a big performance from the former
walk-on named after the '70s singing group. (Reese, Atlanta
Journal-Constitution)
</P>
<P>
   FBC-PIONEER _ After losing 18 starters from last year's team,
including NFL draftee Wilmont Perry at running back, Livingstone
was expected to be facing a major rebuilding job this season.
Instead, the small school from North Carolina has rebounded to earn
a spot in the Pioneer Bowl for the second straight year. Most of
the team's success has centered on the performance of Perry's
replacements _ true freshmen Carlton Jones and Ray Chambers, who
have combined to rush for nearly 2,000 yards. (Reese, Atlanta
Journal-Constitution)
</P>
<P>
   BKC-FRESNO _ Controversy has always seemed to follow Fresno
State coach Jerry Tarkanian. Beginning with his days at Long Beach
State, continuing with UNLV and now at Fresno, Tarkanian has always
had players who had their problems with the law and he has had a
long-time feud with the NCAA. Last season's Fresno State squad
received nationwide attention after a CBS news special profiled its
problems off the court. Despite his troubles, Tarkanian always
seems to field one of the best teams in college basketball. His
latest edition will meet Georgia Saturday in the Delta Air Lines
Classic. (Wilkinson, Atlanta Journal-Constitution)
</P>
<P>
   BKC-KENTUCKY _ After losing several key starters from last
year's national championship team, Kentucky coach Tubby Smith was
forced to look for a leader of this year's Wildcat team. The leader
has emerged in the form of Heshimu Evans, the former transfer from
Manhattan University who has become the team's leading scorer.
Evans is averaging 15.5 points per game and scored 31 points in a
key victory over Maryland earlier this week. Evans will lead the
Wildcats into Saturday's game against Georgia Tech in the Delta Air
Lines Classic. (Schlabach, Atlanta Journal-Constitution).
</P>
<P>
   BKC-GGATECH-COLLIER _ Georgia Tech junior Jason Collier, who has
played two games for the Jackets since gaining his eligibility, is
suffering from bleeding ulcers, but isn't expected to miss
Saturday's game against Kentucky. (Arey, Atlanta
Journal-Constitution). 8.
</P>
<P>
   BKN-NBA-LASTTRY _ In an apparent last-ditch effort to save the
NBA season, Commissioner David Stern takes his message directly to
the players, mailing each a nine-page letter outlining the owners'
latest contract proposal and asking them to consider the offer
individually. (Denberg, Atlanta Journal-Constitution). 10-12.
</P>
<P>
   BBA-RICKY-WILLIAMS _ The Texas Rangers present Ricky Williams
with his first Rangers jersey and cap. Texas picked up the Heisman
Trophy winner's contract from the Montreal Expos earlier this week.
Developing. (Cantu, Austin American-Statesman).
</P>
