   CHRISTMAS-LAS VEGAS &QL;
</P>
<P>
   LAS VEGAS _ It's Christmas morning, and hundreds of twinkling
lights dance, the aroma of roasting turkey whets the appetites of
all, while from everywhere else comes the clanging of quarters
spilling into a hundred coin trays. What's wrong with this picture?
Absolutely nothing. It's Christmas in Las Vegas, and nothing could
be better. By MICHAEL GERST. Story has moved in ``t'' travel
category. &QL; 
 &QL; 
 &QL;
</P>
