   &UR;  &LR; For questions about stories, contact  &UR; Frank Perrotta  &LR; at the
Boston Globe,  &UR; 617-929-2597. &LR;  For individual purchase of graphics
or photos please call 212 556-4204 or -1927.
</P>
<P>
   All stories will bear the BOS designator.
</P>
<P>
   &UR;  &LR;
</P>
<P>
   &UR; INTERNATIONAL (i) &LR;
</P>
<P>
   IRAQ-ATTACKS (Baghdad) -- Explosions and volleys of
anti-aircraft fire rock central Baghdad as the US, Britain launch a
second wave of attacks. By Charles M. Sennott. 1500 words.
</P>
<P>
   IRAQ-BUTLER (New York) -- Russian wants UN chief weapons
inspector Richard Butler replaced over his role in the air strikes
against Baghdad. By Colum Lynch. 800 words.
</P>
<P>
   IRAQ-RUSSIA (Moscow) _ Angered over the strikes against Iraq,
Russia's leaders condemn the move with a vituperation not heard
since the Cold War. By David Filipov. 750 words.
</P>
<P>
   IRAQ-BRITAIN (London) -- While Prime Minister Tony Blair stands
shoulder to shoulder with Bill Clinton, the British people are
divided over the strikes. By Kevin Cullen. 900 words.
</P>
<P>
   &UR; IMPEACHMENT (w) &LR;
</P>
<P>
   IMPEACH-HOUSE (Washington) -- House struggles over when to
proceed with impeachment debate, passes resolution praising
American troops. By Bob Hohler. 1500 words.
</P>
<P>
   IMPEACH-CLINTON (Washington) -- White House struggles to deal
with twin crises, including answering the question of when did
Richard Butler's report become the bar for immediately bombing
Iraq. By Ann Scales. 1200 words.
</P>
<P>
   &UR; NATIONAL (a) &LR;
</P>
<P>
   ASTHMA-SYMPTOMS (Undated) -- Scientists shut down asthma
symptoms in mice by blocking a single chemical messenger in the
immune system, raising the prospect of new, finely tuned drugs to
treat the burdensome disease affecting 15 million Americans. By
Richard Saltus. 700 words.
</P>
<P>
   &UR; FINANCIAL (f) &LR;
</P>
<P>
   IRAQ-MARKET (New York) _ Bombs are flying in the Middle East,
the leader of the free world could be brought down by impeachment,
and the stock market is ... going up? Political shocks aren't quite
the trauma they used to be on Wall Street. By Peter G. Gosselin.
950 words.
</P>
<P>
   STAPLES-CHARGE (Undated) -- Staples to take $57 million
fourth-quarter charge to close 58 outdated stores. In addition,
Staples.com will become separate division. By Chris Reidy. 550
words.
</P>
<P>
   &UR; SPORTS (s) &LR;
</P>
<P>
   FBN-PATRIOTS (Undated) -- The Patriots spend most of their media
session responding to questions about their opponents. At least
during the buildup to Sunday's game against the 49ers, the Patriots
will be in a supporting role. By Frank Dell'Apa. 450 words.
</P>
<P>
   HKN-OTTAWA-BRUINS (Boston) _ By Nancy Marrapese.
