<HEADLINE>
SPANISH JUDGE SAID TO BE PREPARING STRONGER CASE AGAINST PINOCHET 
</HEADLINE>
  (htv) 
 c.1998 N.Y. Times News Service    
<TEXT>
<P>
   MADRID, Spain _ The Spanish judge who issued the arrest warrant
for Gen. Augusto Pinochet in October expects to present an even
stronger case against the former Chilean dictator when England's
Law Lords reconsider his immunity from arrest, a Madrid court
official said Thursday.
</P>
<P>
   The official, speaking on condition of anonymity, said the
285-page indictment provides more specifics than the arrest warrant
and extradition request filed earlier by the judge, Baltasar
Garzon, who indicted Pinochet on Dec. 10, after the Law Lords ruled
on Nov. 25 that he had no immunity from prosecution. On Thursday
they rejected their earlier ruling.
</P>
<P>
   The indictment lays out the most detailed case to date against
Pinochet for the crimes of ``genocide, terrorism and torture,'' the
official said.
</P>
