   WAR-WEDDING (McChord AFB, Wash.) _ Senior Airman Manolito
Carrabis and Faith Schuerch had a lovely wedding planned for
Saturday _ but President Clinton's decision to launch air strikes
on Iraq got in the way. The Air Force told Carrabis he was being
deployed to the Persian Gulf perhaps as early as this Friday, so
they had a hurry-up wedding at McChord Air Force Base on Thursday.
Now, instead of a honeymoon, the happy couple are spending their
last few hours together trying to call Saturday's wedding guests
and tell them they're already married (even the bridesmaid still
doesn't know).
</P>
